  "source_id": "ovarian-cancer",
  "name": "Ovarian Cancer - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + Meds + Labs + Procedures)",
  "description": "Simulates a gyn-oncologist identifying their complete ovarian cancer patient population. Combines: ovarian cancer diagnosis codes, chemotherapy + PARP inhibitor, elevated CA-125, and oophorectomy/hysterectomy procedures. **Third 4-resource-type comprehensive query** in the suite (after CRC and Prostate Cancer).",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete ovarian cancer patient population for a quality improvement initiative on chemotherapy adherence and CA-125 surveillance. From clinical experience, ovarian cancer patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal ovarian cancer diagnosis (often histology-specific), most are on chemotherapy (carboplatin, paclitaxel, cisplatin, gemcitabine, or olaparib), most have undergone oophorectomy or hysterectomy, and most have elevated CA-125.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any ovarian cancer diagnosis\n2. Patients prescribed ovarian cancer chemotherapy\n3. Patients who have undergone oophorectomy or hysterectomy\n4. Patients with elevated CA-125 (>35 U/mL)\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found. Note: this is a female-only population.",
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "multi_query": true,
    "algorithm_path": "comprehensive",
    "algorithm_path_description": "Union of ovarian cancer dx + chemo Rx + surgical Procedures + elevated CA-125. **Third 4-resource-type union test** in the suite (after CRC and Prostate).",
